---
description: Commit working changes frequently; do not let large uncommitted diffs accumulate
alwaysApply: true
---

# Commit Often

- Commit after each logical unit of work lands (feature slice, fix, test pass, docs update).
- Do not accumulate large uncommitted diffs across sessions — push incremental progress instead.
- Before ending a session or switching tasks, commit anything that builds and passes existing tests.
- Ask the user before committing only when they have not requested commits in the current task; when they say "commit", do it without further confirmation.
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, keys, credentials). `.env.example` is fine.
- Write commit messages that explain why, not just what changed.
